<%# The standard closing row of a task-style form (one you enter, then finish or
    abandon): the primary submit plus an explicit "Abbrechen" that navigates back
    without saving — so backing out never depends on finding the page header's
    back link again (#65). Render with `render layout:` when the form also carries
    extra actions (e.g. the saved-filter form's danger delete); the block's
    content lands after the pair, and anything .danger/.delete is pushed to the
    row's far end by the CSS. Label i18n inside a block must use ABSOLUTE keys
    (see the page_header gotcha). %>
<%# locals: (form:, submit_label:, cancel_path:) %>
<div class="form-actions">
  <%= form.submit submit_label, class: 'button-small primary' %>
  <%= link_to t('shared.cancel'), cancel_path, class: 'button-small' %>
  <%= yield if block_given? %>
</div>
